race.comment: AHHA AHHA (8) looks set to break through. She just missed the progressive Davida at Geelong when last seen  with that horse well fancied in the Autumn Stakes earlier. That was a strongly run race and sets her up nicely going to 1600m for the first time. She drops 5kg off a lovely draw and can get the job done. SNEAKY SUNRISE (6) continues to race well, just finding an in form horse a touch too strong at Flemington last time out. She can land in a trailing position here and prove hard to hold out. HIYAAM PROUD (7) was poor in the same race at Flemington but had been knocking on the door prior and can bounce back. Watch the market with UK import PANTILE WARRIOR (10) for the Danny O'Brien yard. He'll get further but has run well over shorter trips and  has the ability to give this a shake if right. VERDAD (1) is consistent and an each way hope again.
